EmoteActions.Message: I find a flaming skull is the best way to deter a hostile creature from attacking you!
Carving a fierce face into a scarecrow head is a sure way to make your opponent dread the fate headed towards them.
Well here goes nothing. Okay paring knife to make the eyes... whoops! No problem, no problem. Yeah that works. Whew!
There you go. See, just like Janda's.
Now let's see, carving knife into the skull to separate the... No that doesn't look right. What about? Nope. Hmm. Oh yeah I had the directions upside down.
Quite simple actually.
Ahh, I have been expecting to see some of these soon. I'll be with you in a moment.
%n begins work on the mask. For a moment the mask looks more like a mummy than a virindi.
Whoops!
Heh, tell your friends. I'm improving, aren't I?
Thank you for having the same faith in my skills as Janda. It makes me happy to know that... Oops...
In his zeal, Bleis accidentally gouges the gauntlets.
I'm so sorry! I don't think the gauntlets are damaged badly, if anything they will just be lightly scarred.

Hello, I'm Bleis, Janda's apprentice.  She's letting me work with skulls, scarecrow heads, mosswart heads, and baderling heads. Finally! Of course I'm still learning, I never thought that apprenticeship would take so long. I'll craft the older versions of the mosswart and banderling masks for you. If you would like the old styles or something unique hand one of the heads to me.

Also, with Janda's blessing, I am learning the art of facetting. She believes I am capable of applying what I have learned. If you have them handy, I will be happy to alter your Sunstone Gauntlets and bring a dark red color to them.

Making masks is a noble pursuit.  While researching it, I learned how to bring out the inner magic in skeleton skulls.  This ability also works on scarecrow heads, but only during the Festival Season.
